Wash and dry all produce. Adjust broiler rack so that it is in position closest to
flame and place a #baking sheet{} on rack. Preheat broiler to high. Core and dice
@Roma Tomato{1}(diced). Thinly slice @Scallions{2}(sliced), separating greens and
whites. Tear @Pulled Pork{10%ounce} into larger bite-size pieces.

Heat @Butter{1%tablespoon} and @Olive Oil{1%tablespoon} in a large pan over
medium-high heat. Stir in @Sweet and Smoky BBQ Seasoning{1%tablespoon}. Cook
until fragrant, about ~{30%seconds}.

Add pulled pork and @water{1/4%cup} to pan, stirring to coat. Cook, stirring
occasionally, until warmed through and water is mostly evaporated but still a
little saucy, ~{2-3%minutes}. Season with @Salt{} and @Pepper{}.

Scatter pork evenly over @Flatbreads{2}, then repeat with tomato, scallion whites,
and @Mozzarella Cheese{1/2%cup}. Carefully remove baking sheet from broiler and
sprinkle with a drizzle of @Olive Oil{2%teaspoon}.

> TIP: Get out your mitts; the sheet will be hot.

Transfer flatbreads to sheet and sprinkle each with a large drizzle of
@Olive Oil{2%teaspoon}.

Return baking sheet to broiler and broil until cheese melts and flatbreads begin
to turn golden brown and crisp, ~{3-4%minutes}.

> TIP: Keep an eye on these; they can burn easily.

Drizzle @BBQ Sauce{2%ounce} over flatbreads and sprinkle with scallion greens.
Cut into slices and serve.